                    <section class="legal-section">
                        <h2 class="legal-heading">Security measures used</h2>
                        <strong>SSL and TLS encryption</strong>
                        <p>
                            This site uses SSL or TLS encryption to protect the transmission of content. You can
                            recognise this by the fact that the address line of the browser begins with ‘https://’.
                            In particular, the system automatically switches from an unencrypted to an encrypted
                            connection. This means that no data can be read by third parties.
                        </p><br>
                        <strong>Hard drive encryption</strong>
                        <p>
                            All data is stored on encrypted data carriers. This protects your data from unauthorised
                            removal and reading of the data carriers, even if the data can no longer be deleted due
                            to a defect.
                        </p>
                    </section>

